6	features	About SLOtility	\r\n# Feeling full helps you manage your weight\r\n## If you eat foods which move slowly through your stomach, you will feel more full, eat less and maintain a healthier weight\r\n\r\nThe name SLOtility comes from wanting to slow down stomach motility while eating.  As such, SLOtility is based on the concept that if you eat foods which move slowly through your stomach, you will feel more full, eat less and maintain a healthier weight.  We all know that most diets fail when people ‘fall off the wagon’ and eventually start to eat more food.  Therefore, any successful diet regimen must address satiety, as feeling full will be a natural safeguard against eating too much.  SLOtility also serves a metabolic function: slowing food down in your stomach slows food absorption , thereby lowering blood sugar and hormone levels after eating, which over time can reduce risk of chronic disease.\r\nSo SLOtility consists of all the natural foods and eating techniques that have been shown to slow food down in your stomach.  Here are some examples: soluble fiber sits in your  stomach longer, so the diet lists which foods have the highest soluble fiber content; vinegar and cinnamon also slow food in your stomach, so the diet has regimens and ways to incorporate these into your diet.  So you can then start to phase these into your diet: maybe eating oatmeal instead of rice krispies; or if you already eat oatmeal, mixing cinnamon into it; and eating a salad with heavy vinaigrette instead of cooked vegetables with dinner.  Keep in mind the goal is to habituate these techniques, so then you no longer have to think or decide, but you will automatically use SLOtility techniques\r\n\r\n# We need your help\r\n## We need everyone who tries a SLOtility Supplement regimen to share their results on this platform, and together we will create the world’s first crowdsourced diet!  \r\n\r\nA crowdsourced diet is optimized and evolved as more and more people try SLOtility Supplements and enter their feedback.  The feedback data is aggregated and analyzed to see which supplements are working the best.  For example, let's say we have 100 people taking vinegar, and 100 people taking cinnamon, and we start to see that people are having better results using vinegar (e.g. losing more weight, lower blood sugar, etc).  Then we can use that data to prioritize taking vinegar, or perhaps then to look at combining cinnamon with another SLOtility Supplement to see if results will improve.  The point is, no one knows how the diet will optimize- you, the crowd are going to steer the diet forward!\r\nWhen you sign up for SLOtility, it is a 1 month program where you choose which of the SLOtility Supplements you want to try, and you may track whatever profile data you are interested in, including weight, blood pressure, sugar, and/or cholesterol.  All you have to do for the month is keep track of how many days of the month you take the supplement regimen, and then enter your results at the end of the month.  We will help you every step of the way, including: regimen suggestions, mobile device reminders and data entry, and feedback to help you calibrate your diet to reach your goals and stay healthy.  At the same time, the website will store your results and combine them with others' to see if any data trends show that some SLOtility Supplements are working better than others.  The key to the crowdsourced diet is the power of numbers! \r\nSo together we can create a large crowd on the internet which will generate enough statistical power to verify and evolve which SLOtility Supplements work the best. The SLOtility program is unique in that not only can you use the diet to improve your health, but you can at the same time help to crowdsource the diet itself.  So, sign up today and let's use the internet to revolutionize dieting!\r\n\r\n# Works with any diet or eating style\r\n## SLOtility foods, eating techniques, and supplements will help you to feel more full and eat less regardless of what you eat.\r\n\r\nSLOtility is a cataloguing of foods and eating techniques which you can incorporate into the way you’re eating now in order to slow food down in your stomach and help manage your weight.  You don't have to radically change your eating style, but rather you can simply cut back on your portion sizes, and SLOtility techniques and Supplements will help you feel satisfied while eating less.  See the list of supplements at [/interventions] \r\n\r\n# Lower risk of common diseases - beyond weight loss\r\n## SLOtility includes 16 Xtra Supplements to help reduce your risk of Diabetes, High Blood Pressure, and Heart Disease\r\n\r\nThe SLOtility Diet program has 13 supplements which slow your food down- we call these the SLOtility Basics.  Slowing food down in ur stomach not only helps you to eat less while feeling satisfied, but also slows food absorption, thereby lowering blood sugar and hormone levels after eating, which over time can help stave off the onset of chronic disease. To add to this effect, we have also included supplement components to the SLOtility Diet which help lower blood pressure, blood sugar, and blood cholesterol, all of which can help reduce risk of diabetes, high blood pressure, and heart disease, which are 3 of the most common serious health problems facing our country.\r\n\r\nWe call these extra supplements the SLOtility Xtras, and anyone who wants to track their own blood pressure, blood sugar (or HgbA1C), or blood cholesterol can sign up for one month of these supplement regimens.  We will then crowdsource everyone’s results to see which SLOtility Xtras work the best to maintain your health!  Keep in mind that if your goal is simply to track your weight, we have the SLOtility Basic supplements to choose from which you can use to specifically slow your food down and help to manage your weight.  In this way, the SLO-tility Diet can cater to your personal goals and what you wish to track, be it weight or health measurements, which will help you to both manage your weight and maintain your health!\r\n\r\n# Pay what you wish\r\n##SLOtility.com has been [crowdfunded](http://www.indiegogo.com/projects/slo-tility-com-the-world-s-first-crowdsourced-diet) , crowdsourced, and crowdfriendly.  We follow this philosophy by letting the crowd decide what this program is worth to each and every one of you\r\n\r\nOur philosophy at SLOtility.com is that everybody gives and everybody gets.  Indeed at our origins, we crowdfunded the project in fundraising style: give a little to the project and get a little in return (like a SLOtility tshirt, now a collectors item!?...).  And, as promised, we mention all the contributors here:\r\ninchworms: allen (aces) hieppham; effross (the theorist)\r\nslugs: dreppert (the computer guy) 1; carol (the best CM) 0616; caralyng (baker extaordinaire) 24; PoetSmurf (kind to the animals) _100\r\nsnails:  sarakim (california girl) 1024; djl ((one of) the best student(s)) 0516; jersey (he literally had guts) mf; sarah (bare) knuckles; roebuck (ur mom is cool) _sarah; kdiegel (the marathon girl) 1120\r\ntortoisii: rcw (Hudson River Watch) 320; rg (Robin the stomach superhero) christner; Anthony (the Philosopher King) Bufort; gharry (the Quizzo Champ) br\r\nsloth: David (Vegan is Virtue) Seelig\r\nglacier: bxdafei (the Oak) .1- ur indeed the foundation and this project’s progress and flowering grow out of your roots- thanx Dad :)\r\n\r\nSLOtility's success will be to the indebtedness to all our users, and we hope that the whole will be greater than the sum of its parts for its value in contributing to improving public health. \r\nSLOtility is dedicated to Irene Flora Castle Duffy - her love, support, intellect, and fierce imperative to know and to have the courage to do the right thing is the wellspring of my character- and as this project succeeds in improving public health, it owes its inspiration to that imperative- thanx Mom-  fduf\r\n\r\n# About us - a Diet born in Philly\r\n## We are a new diet concept out of Philadelphia, now online with a platform to help as many people as possible manage their weight and decrease their risk of chronic disease through healthier eating habits.\r\n\r\n###The Unofficial AutoBiography\r\nWho's the guy with the sideburns in [the video](http://philadelphia.cbslocal.com/2013/11/08/health-diet-trick-you-probably-never-heard-of/)? No, it's not a stunt double- it's me, Frank Duffy: native of Jersey, now in Philly. Nutritionist by trade and moonlight as an intellectual. Work with patients, students, and a little bit of research. Traveled to Ghana and lived in Chicago and Kentucky, but couldn't shed Northeastern roots. Interested in public health and specialize in diabetes. Self proclaimed pinball wizard who had 15 minutes (ok, seconds) of fame appearing on MTV news' coverage of a pinball tournament at the old Broadway Arcade (back when MTV was cool and played music…\r\n\r\n###The Nutriculum Vitae\r\nHere's the gist of my research in nutrition.  My main interests are diabetes and GI nutrition:\r\n“[Dietary Treatment for Gastroparesis](http://books.google.com/books?id#E2t1VL8wEzYC&pg#PA237&lpg#PA237&dq#frank+duffy+gastroparesis&source#bl&ots#62j8NDgIrw&sig#aBeWoMDslDAidcOYYT6eV7TVnMM&hl#en&sa#X&ei#GOHyUc_UKvGr4AOipYCYAg&ved#0CFIQ6AEwAg#v#onepage&q#frank%20duffy%20gastroparesis&f#false)" In Gastroparesis, edited by Henry P. Parkman and Richard W McCallum, 237-256. New York: Humana Press, 2012. (when I started to research SLOtility: the concept of slowing food down in the stomach)\r\nNIH sponsored research on [blood sugar responses to different macronutrient loads](http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10620-011-1810-z#page-1) (where I got the idea for vinegar as a SLOtility Basic Supplement)\r\nNIDDK GpCRC [research on nutritional status in gastroparesis](http://pubmedcentralcanada.ca/pmcc/articles/PMC3499101/) \r\n\r\n### The Modus Operandi\r\nThe purpose of this project is to serve the public interest by reducing the risk of diabetes, hypertension, and heart disease in the general public.  Our healthcare system is buckling under the cost of treatment- healthcare reform must create preventative models which educate and empower citizens to develop healthy lifestyle habits and stave off the burden of chronic illness.  SLOtility will use an internet platform as a vector to help as many people as possible decrease their risk through healthier eating habits.  That is our goal and, with your help, we will achieve it- one slug at a time (so to speak...)	2014-01-14 15:40:20.233674	2014-01-14 15:50:16.10878
7	steps	Steps for SLOtility - a monthly cycle	## The SLOtility program consists of 3 steps: 1. entering your starting info, 2. picking a supplement regimen to take every day for one month; and 3. recording your results at the end of the month.\r\n\r\n## Step 1\r\nAs you sign up, we will collect your profile data: demographic info and any health data you want to track, including weight, blood pressure, blood sugar, and blood cholesterol.  Analyzing your profile, we will estimate your risk of diabetes, high blood pressure, heart disease, and obesity, Based on your risk we will recommend an appropriate list of SLOtility Supplements to choose from, with all the info on how to take them and safety precautions…\r\n\r\nWe collect demographic info and health data such as weight, blood pressure, cholesterol; We analyze your profile and recommend supplements to choose from and how to take them.\r\n\r\n## Step 2\r\nYou will pick a SLOtility Supplement regimen to take every day for one month- so only pick what you know you can do for a month!  Make sure to get the supplements at home so you’re ready to start. Once you start, just keep track of how many days you take the supplement- we will mobile/computer message daily to remind you, and you can click yea or nay and that’s it!\r\n\r\n## Step 3\r\nAt the end of the month, you enter in your results that you’re tracking: your current weight, your current blood pressure, etc.  And along with everyone else’s data, we will crowdsource the results to prime the next month’s cycle!	2014-01-14 15:51:50.1971	2014-01-14 15:53:17.23382
9	intro	Overview and Introduction to SLOtility	The SLOtility Diet is based on the concept that if you eat foods which move slowly through your stomach, you will feel more full and eat less, thus helping you manage your weight without the need to starve yourself or count every calorie. We have structured the diet around two components, the SLOtility Diet Eating Style and the SLOtility Diet Supplements.\r\n\r\n### Changing eating habits\r\nThe SLOtility Eating Style focuses on changing your overall eating habits and consists of all the natural foods and eating techniques that have been shown to slow food down in your stomach. When practiced on a regular basis, you will find yourself feeling less hungry throughout the day and less likely to eat too much during meals. The result of this will help you maintain a healthy weight and reduce your risk of chronic disease.\r\n\r\n### SLOtility Eating Style\r\nIn order to help you to kickstart the SLOtility Eating Style, we have incorporated the SLOtility Supplements: 29 natural supplements with easy-to-follow instructions which you can start at the beginning of our monthly cycle. These supplements are subdivided into two broad categories, "SLOtility BASICS" and "SLOtility XTRAS," which together reflect the two goals of our diet plan: managing your weight and maintaining your health.\r\n\r\nWe all know that most diets fail when people "fall off the wagon" and eventually start to eat more food. Therefore, any successful diet regimen must address satiety, as feeling full will be a natural safeguard against eating too much. The 13 SLOtility BASICS form the cornerstone of the SLOtility Eating Style. Each of these supplements has been demonstrated to slow food down in your stomach, and will help you Manage Your Weight.\r\n\r\nIn addition to making you feel less hungry, slowing down the passage of food in your stomach also serves a metabolic function by slowing down food absorption, thereby lowering blood sugar and hormone levels after eating, which over time can reduce the risk of chronic disease. To add to this effect, we have also included 16 additional supplements, called SLOtility XTRAS, which will help you Maintain Your Health by reducing your risk for diabetes, high blood pressure, and heart disease, which are 3 of the most common serious health problems facing our country.\r\n\r\n### Monthly cycles\r\nWe structured the SLOtility crowdsourcing diet and our website so that each month represents a new diet cycle. By synchronizing everyone's starting day to the same time, we hope it will be easier for everyone to complete the program together and to foster a community of dieters all of whom share the common goal to be healthier. We can all help each other achieve this goal, whether this is by participating in the online forums, or simply by entering in your health information and logging your supplements on your site account (we are integrating our site with mobile devices to make this really easy!). At the end of the month, we will use all this data from the crowd to let everyone know which supplements worked the best for everyone, and to personalize recommendations for you going forward. To generate this information, all the data we collect from you will go into an anonymous database- it will always be up to you what information you wish to share with your fellow dieters. Your privacy is very important to us at SLOtility.com.\r\n\r\n### Profiles\r\nEveryone can sign up and fill out their profile so they are ready to start. However, we are asking everyone to prepare now so that you are ready to go when the site goes live within the next few weeks. This will include collecting any health information that you wish to track, which is important for monitoring your health and weight loss progress, and also choosing which of the 29 supplements that fits best with your tastes and health goals (you can choose as many as you want, but one is fine too!). In addition to your weight, you are invited to also track your waist/hip circumference, blood pressure, blood sugar, hemoglobin A1C levels, and blood cholesterol. If you don't know your numbers, you can measure them at your doctor's or at a clinic, or you can buy your own monitors online or at a drugstore and measure them at home. Many drugstores also have free-to-use blood pressure monitors.\r\n\r\nAs for the SLOtility Supplements, right now is a good time to select the one or more you'd like to take for our first SLOtility monthly cycle, starting early next month (December). Only choose ones that you know you can take every day for 28 days (4 weeks). For those of you whose primary goal is to manage your weight,we recommend focusing on the 13 SLOtility BASICS, as these have been specifically chosen based on their action of slowing stomach motility. For those of you who seek to reduce your risk for diabetes, high blood pressure, and heart disease, you can select from the set of 16 SLOtility XTRAS, based on your specific needs. We have included a comprehensive chart on the next page to guide your selection of supplements based on for which medical condition(s) each has been demonstrated to reduce risk.\r\nWhen the site goes live within the next few weeks, the website will use your profile data to calculate your risk for each of these three medical conditions, which will help you decide whether including some of the XTRAS as part of your SLOtility plan is right for you. As with mostly all of the SLOtility Supplements, the XTRAS are natural foods, and keep in mind that they are included here because of their effect on reducing risk for diabetes, heart disease, and/or high blood pressure, as none of the XTRAS have been demonstrated to slow stomach motility. If your main reason for signing up for the SLOtility Diet is to manage your weight but you would like to also reduce your risk for these medical conditions, note that four of the BASICS have also been shown to reduce risk for diabetes, heart disease, and blood pressure, though three of the BASICS are contraindicated for those with high blood pressure (again, see the included chart on the next page for a guide).\r\n\r\n### Customized\r\nWe engineered the SLOtility Diet to be customizable for each participant based on his or her specific health needs and dietary goals. By helping people transition to a healthier eating style while introducing natural foods and eating techniques that will make managing weight easier and hunger free, and by utilizing a crowdsourcing website to foster a community of like-minded dieters, we hope to start a movement towards more sustainable dieting free of the on/off trends and struggles of many other diet plans.\r\n\r\nOur healthcare system is buckling under the cost of treatment and healthcare reform must create preventative models which educate and empower citizens to develop healthy lifestyle habits and stave off the burden of chronic illness. The SLOtility diet will use an internet platform as a vector to help as many people as possible decrease their risk through healthier eating habits. That is our goal and, with your help, we will achieve it- slooooowly...\r\n\r\n	2014-01-14 17:20:27.382656	2014-01-14 17:44:18.243723
